### The ingame overlay:

![Overlay](http://i.imgur.com/3ZX9Elm.jpg "The overlay")

#### Card Marks
Opponent hand cards are denoted with icons
* ![Coin](https://github.com/Epix37/Hearthstone-Deck-Tracker/blob/master/Hearthstone%20Deck%20Tracker/Images/card-icon-coin.png "Coin") - coin
* ![Mulligan](https://github.com/Epix37/Hearthstone-Deck-Tracker/blob/master/Hearthstone%20Deck%20Tracker/Images/card-icon-mulligan.png "Mulligan") - mulliganed
* ![Returned](https://github.com/Epix37/Hearthstone-Deck-Tracker/blob/master/Hearthstone%20Deck%20Tracker/Images/card-icon-returned.png "Returned") - returned (e.g. by youthful brewmaster)
* ![Gift](https://github.com/Epix37/Hearthstone-Deck-Tracker/blob/master/Hearthstone%20Deck%20Tracker/Images/card-icon-created.png "Gift") - created cards (e.g. spare parts)

#### Adjusting positions & deck list
* Everything in the overlay can be moved around by unlocking it in the options menu: 
![unlock](http://i.imgur.com/9ut1DZt.png)

* What's displayed in the deck list can be moved around and turned on/off separately, too:
![unlock](http://i.imgur.com/kxjeQjZ.png)  
(same goes for the opponent, one item lower in the list on the left)
